        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 22 at 2:55PM CST by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 255 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake City, or near Mathis, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mathis, Lake City, Sandia, Argenta, Lagarto, Mount Lucas, Dinero,
Lakeside, Lake Corpus Christi, and Pernitas Point.

This includes Interstate 37 between mile markers 38 and 48.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
